      <p class="lead">
        Most people think facial aging is only about skin.
        <br />
        But in reality, it’s about <strong>structure, balance, and how your face is supported from within.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>What does a “harmonious face” actually mean?</h2>
      <p>
        A harmonious face is not about perfection or symmetry.
        It’s about <strong>balance</strong>.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>The proportions between the upper, middle, and lower face</li>
        <li>A defined yet natural jawline</li>
        <li>Soft but supported facial volume</li>
        <li>Relaxed muscles without excessive tension</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        When these elements are aligned, the face appears 
        <strong>fresh, lifted, and naturally attractive.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>Why does the face lose harmony?</h2>
      <p>
        Over time, the face changes — but not only because of age.
        <br />
        <strong>Daily habits play a much bigger role than most people realize.</strong>
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Mouth breathing instead of nasal breathing</li>
        <li>Incorrect tongue posture</li>
        <li>Chronic muscle tension</li>
        <li>Poor posture and head position</li>
        <li>Stress and unconscious facial habits</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        All of this gradually affects the structure of the face.
        The lower face may become heavier, the jawline less defined,
        and the overall expression more tired.
      </p>

      <h2>It’s not just aging</h2>
      <p>
        This is important to understand:
      </p>

      <p class="highlight">
        Your face is not only changing because of time.
        <br />
        It’s changing because of how you use it every day.
      </p>

      <h2>Can this be improved?</h2>
      <p>
        Yes — and this is where most people are surprised.
      </p>

      <p>
        You don’t always need aggressive procedures to support your face.
        <br />
        When you start working with your anatomy — <strong>gently and consistently</strong> —
        you can improve balance, support, and natural facial volume.
      </p>

      <h2>A natural approach</h2>
      <p>
        Facial Volume Harmony is a structured system designed to support your face from within.
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Awareness of facial habits</li>
        <li>Correct tongue posture and breathing</li>
